And Candace Pert talked
about the neural peptides,

00:10:49.690 --> 00:10:53.160 align:middle line:84%
the protein molecules,
the tiny kinase

00:10:53.160 --> 00:10:58.210 align:middle line:84%
signals going in between the
cells, and they also retain.

00:10:58.210 --> 00:11:03.710 align:middle line:84%
So if you use a language,
I'm crazy, I'm sick,

00:11:03.710 --> 00:11:05.920 align:middle line:84%
nobody likes me,
nobody loves me,

00:11:05.920 --> 00:11:08.500 align:middle line:84%
that memory is retained
on a cellular level that

00:11:08.500 --> 00:11:10.096 align:middle line:90%
affects the membrane.

00:11:10.096 --> 00:11:12.230 align:middle line:84%
>> And then this is
passed on subsequently?

00:11:12.230 --> 00:11:13.030 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:11:13.030 --> 00:11:17.470 align:middle line:84%
So they had a town in
Sweden that some researcher

00:11:17.470 --> 00:11:21.160 align:middle line:84%
found that kept meticulous
records for over 200 years

00:11:21.160 --> 00:11:22.840 align:middle line:90%
about all the residents.

00:11:22.840 --> 00:11:25.400 align:middle line:84%
And they didn't have
a lot of immigration.

00:11:25.400 --> 00:11:28.720 align:middle line:84%
So the data was sent to
Cambridge University,

00:11:28.720 --> 00:11:30.130 align:middle line:90%
which analyzed it.

00:11:30.130 --> 00:11:33.460 align:middle line:84%
And they found what was
going on in that town

00:11:33.460 --> 00:11:36.100 align:middle line:84%
with the residents of the
town and with their help

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:37.990 align:middle line:84%
was affected by
signals that were

00:11:37.990 --> 00:11:40.270 align:middle line:90%
coming from the grandparents.

00:11:40.270 --> 00:11:43.870 align:middle line:84%
So in females, it would come
from the maternal grandmother

00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:48.160 align:middle line:84%
when she was in gestation
with her mother,

00:11:48.160 --> 00:11:49.500 align:middle line:90%
so the great-grandmother.

00:11:49.500 --> 00:11:53.890 align:middle line:84%
So what the great-grandmother
was experiencing

00:11:53.890 --> 00:11:56.860 align:middle line:84%
would be passed on
to the grandchild

00:11:56.860 --> 00:11:58.150 align:middle line:90%
on the maternal side.

00:11:58.150 --> 00:12:01.090 align:middle line:84%
So if she was living
a life of excess--

00:12:01.090 --> 00:12:02.800 align:middle line:90%
there was plenty of food--

00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:06.380 align:middle line:84%
they would have
diseases of excess.

00:12:06.380 --> 00:12:07.360 align:middle line:90%
>> Two generations?

00:12:07.360 --> 00:12:08.990 align:middle line:90%
>> Two generations.

00:12:08.990 --> 00:12:12.250 align:middle line:84%
Now in boys it was different,
it was the paternal grandfather

00:12:12.250 --> 00:12:15.490 align:middle line:90%
at puberty that was passed on.

00:12:15.490 --> 00:12:21.340 align:middle line:84%
So if there was a
period of starvation

00:12:21.340 --> 00:12:25.670 align:middle line:84%
the boys were having, you would
have diseases of retention,

00:12:25.670 --> 00:12:28.360 align:middle line:84%
which would predispose
people to chronic disease,

00:12:28.360 --> 00:12:32.020 align:middle line:84%
because the body
would store too much.

00:12:32.020 --> 00:12:33.670 align:middle line:90%
And I had a case like that--

00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:36.640 align:middle line:84%
I think it's on my website,
or at least I wrote about it--

00:12:36.640 --> 00:12:43.260 align:middle line:84%
where I was referred a girl from
parents who were from Guatemala

00:12:43.260 --> 00:12:45.452 align:middle line:90%
for tremendous weight gain.

00:12:45.452 --> 00:12:46.910 align:middle line:84%
And I thought it
was a simple case,

00:12:46.910 --> 00:12:50.920 align:middle line:84%
it was probably junk food,
she's a teenager, eating poorly.

00:12:50.920 --> 00:12:54.130 align:middle line:84%
And all my assumptions
were completely wrong.

00:12:54.130 --> 00:12:56.860 align:middle line:84%
She comes in,
she's an A student.

00:12:56.860 --> 00:12:59.280 align:middle line:90%
They ate a natural diet.

00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:03.640 align:middle line:84%
She was on the soccer team,
and she was doing well in life.

00:13:03.640 --> 00:13:08.270 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened was
she kept gaining weight,

00:13:08.270 --> 00:13:11.000 align:middle line:84%
and really getting to
a point of obesity.

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:13.900 align:middle line:84%
So I knew this about
the epigenetics.

00:13:13.900 --> 00:13:16.660 align:middle line:90%
And I questioned the mother.

00:13:16.660 --> 00:13:20.200 align:middle line:84%
And I asked her, what was
it like when your mother was

00:13:20.200 --> 00:13:21.630 align:middle line:90%
born to your great-grandmother?

00:13:21.630 --> 00:13:22.880 align:middle line:90%
Do you know anything about it?

00:13:22.880 --> 00:13:23.920 align:middle line:90%
Which was in Guatemala.

00:13:23.920 --> 00:13:27.610 align:middle line:84%
She said, well,
there was 12 children

00:13:27.610 --> 00:13:30.470 align:middle line:84%
and there was never
enough to eat.

00:13:30.470 --> 00:13:33.940 align:middle line:84%
So the epigenetic
signal was transferred

00:13:33.940 --> 00:13:37.840 align:middle line:84%
on to the
granddaughter to store.

00:13:37.840 --> 00:13:41.740 align:middle line:84%
Now we know the actual
biochemical way that happens,

00:13:41.740 --> 00:13:45.430 align:middle line:84%
that the excess is
stored in the fat cells.

00:13:45.430 --> 00:13:46.990 align:middle line:90%
And the fat cells--

00:13:46.990 --> 00:13:49.960 align:middle line:84%
if the liver gives
the wrong signal--

00:13:49.960 --> 00:13:53.290 align:middle line:84%
can expand and become
inflamed as much as 100 times

00:13:53.290 --> 00:13:55.040 align:middle line:90%
its original size.

00:13:55.040 --> 00:13:57.030 align:middle line:84%
And it started
explaining to me why

00:13:57.030 --> 00:14:01.600 align:middle line:84%
I have people coming to see me
who have tremendous obesity,

00:14:01.600 --> 00:14:03.550 align:middle line:84%
and they're in the
gym three hours a day,

00:14:03.550 --> 00:14:05.410 align:middle line:84%
and they're eating
hardly anything,

00:14:05.410 --> 00:14:06.910 align:middle line:90%
and they keep gaining weight.

00:14:06.910 --> 00:14:09.400 align:middle line:84%
Because everything
that they're exposed to

00:14:09.400 --> 00:14:11.987 align:middle line:90%
is stored in the fat cells.

00:14:11.987 --> 00:14:13.570 align:middle line:84%
And you see that now
with the epidemic

00:14:13.570 --> 00:14:16.540 align:middle line:84%
we're having with
estrogen dominance.

00:14:16.540 --> 00:14:18.880 align:middle line:84%
Almost everybody
is under stress.

00:14:18.880 --> 00:14:21.730 align:middle line:84%
The estrogen, which
tells the body build,

00:14:21.730 --> 00:14:26.830 align:middle line:84%
store, and progesterone tells
the body what to build into.

00:14:26.830 --> 00:14:29.530 align:middle line:84%
The progesterone
converts too rapidly

00:14:29.530 --> 00:14:36.370 align:middle line:84%
into cortisol, which is the
sugar mechanism in stress.

00:14:36.370 --> 00:14:39.220 align:middle line:84%
And then the body has
unopposed estrogen.

00:14:39.220 --> 00:14:42.189 align:middle line:84%
You can have low estrogen and
still have estrogen dominance.

00:14:42.189 --> 00:14:44.730 align:middle line:84%
>> And then what are the effects
of estrogen dominance again?

00:14:44.730 --> 00:14:47.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, one of them is thyroid,
because progesterone signals

00:14:47.740 --> 00:14:48.916 align:middle line:90%
the thyroid.

00:14:48.916 --> 00:14:51.040 align:middle line:84%
>> So we have a lot of
hypothyroidism, for example?

00:14:51.040 --> 00:14:53.350 align:middle line:84%
>> We have a lot of hypothyroid,
but it's not coming from

00:14:53.350 --> 00:14:54.150 align:middle line:90%
the thyroid.

00:14:54.150 --> 00:14:55.437 align:middle line:90%
That's why we have it.

00:14:55.437 --> 00:14:57.520 align:middle line:84%
It's the body's saying, I
don't have enough energy

00:14:57.520 --> 00:14:59.960 align:middle line:84%
to keep doing what I am,
I'm going to shut down

00:14:59.960 --> 00:15:01.305 align:middle line:90%
so I don't blow a gasket.

00:15:01.305 --> 00:15:02.215 align:middle line:90%
>> Interesting.

00:15:02.215 --> 00:15:06.340 align:middle line:84%
>> And so it's really an adrenal
problem, a stress problem.

00:15:06.340 --> 00:15:08.140 align:middle line:84%
Because the body's
tearing itself apart,

00:15:08.140 --> 00:15:11.140 align:middle line:84%
it's catabolic, which
means tearing itself apart.

00:15:11.140 --> 00:15:14.270 align:middle line:84%
And when you tear apart your
body, you have to rebuild it.

00:15:14.270 --> 00:15:16.150 align:middle line:84%
So you have to have
the right signals,

00:15:16.150 --> 00:15:18.860 align:middle line:84%
and you have to have the right
nutrients to rebuild yourself.

00:15:18.860 --> 00:15:21.480 align:middle line:84%
So every single day,
you recreate yourself.

00:15:21.480 --> 00:15:23.640 align:middle line:84%
And if you're imbalanced
one way or the other,

00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:25.970 align:middle line:84%
you're going to have
certain problems,

00:15:25.970 --> 00:15:27.690 align:middle line:90%
and that's what we're seeing.

00:15:27.690 --> 00:15:31.790 align:middle line:84%
That's why we're seeing so
much disability, and lack

00:15:31.790 --> 00:15:34.280 align:middle line:84%
of adaptation,
and people looking

00:15:34.280 --> 00:15:37.070 align:middle line:84%
to take drugs or
something to keep

00:15:37.070 --> 00:15:40.640 align:middle line:84%
them going to mitigate
the imbalances that we're

00:15:40.640 --> 00:15:43.850 align:middle line:84%
seeing, which is basically
an allergy to modern life.

00:15:43.850 --> 00:15:47.420 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, exactly, to stress.

00:15:47.420 --> 00:15:51.920 align:middle line:90%
OK, a couple of questions then.

