00:17:57.360 --> 00:18:00.530 align:middle line:84%
>> But to bond the child
so it feels protected.

00:18:00.530 --> 00:18:04.350 align:middle line:84%
So I think-- this
is my own theory--

00:18:04.350 --> 00:18:08.030 align:middle line:84%
that in mammalian
life, what made

00:18:08.030 --> 00:18:11.480 align:middle line:84%
the mother want to
self-sacrifice herself

00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:13.036 align:middle line:90%
for her children?

00:18:13.036 --> 00:18:15.340 align:middle line:90%
It would be oxytocin.

00:18:15.340 --> 00:18:17.840 align:middle line:84%
And what would make her-- if
some predator wanted to eat her

00:18:17.840 --> 00:18:19.060 align:middle line:90%
children--

00:18:19.060 --> 00:18:21.590 align:middle line:84%
the ferocious defender
of her children,

00:18:21.590 --> 00:18:24.130 align:middle line:84%
she had to rapidly
convert it to vasopressin

00:18:24.130 --> 00:18:29.340 align:middle line:84%
to defend the lives of her child
for generations to continue.

00:18:29.340 --> 00:18:35.100 align:middle line:84%
